numbered_ace_sentences: 1. I am sick and tired of hearing about the Ivy League.
2. For the last 47 years, I have taught at a top public university in the world.
3. I have had graduate students from the Ivy League.
4. I think that the privilege of these students has been nauseating.
5. I think that many things have been handed to these students.
6. I think that these students cannot work well in health care.
7. On average, I think that these students have been sheltered.
8. On average, I think that these students cannot tolerate stress well.
12. Many faculty of Duke live hand to mouth on grant funding.
13. I think that Duke is cheap.
14. I think that Duke will not even pay the salaries of its faculty.
15. I think that Duke breeds an unhealthy environment.
